{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":74107,"duration_api_ms":74111,"num_turns":6,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"7079f704-b4bd-4154-9235-425961528789","total_cost_usd":0.33619599999999994,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":23324,"cache_read_input_tokens":176520,"output_tokens":1663,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":23324,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":7,"outputTokens":1663,"cacheReadInputTokens":176520,"cacheCreationInputTokens":23324,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.275645,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":39,"outputTokens":2166,"cacheReadInputTokens":108570,"cacheCreationInputTokens":31060,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.060550999999999994,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"All four amendments identify legitimate issues in the crash-resume and retry machinery. Two are correctness bugs (fr-15-34731127 silently swallowing the critical pre-backoff snapshot write, fr-15-bd667ff0 resetting attempt counters on resume), one is a minor durability/observability gap (fr-15-1822a124 missing write after restoring active_run), and one is a useful diagnostic improvement (fr-15-ea35568a logging signal-killed processes). I agree with the planner positions on all four.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-15-1822a124","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified at engine.rs:4671-4672: after `snapshot.active_run = snapshot.interrupted_run.take()` and `snapshot.status = RunStatus::Running`, there is no write_run_snapshot call before control flows to the top of the next loop iteration. A crash in this window leaves on-disk state as Failed with interrupted_run populated, which is recoverable but inconsistent with in-memory state. External status polling or monitoring would see stale 'Failed' status. Adding a write_run_snapshot here is cheap (one extra disk write per retry cycle) and closes the observability gap. Low risk, clear benefit."},{"amendment_id":"fr-15-ea35568a","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified at process_backend.rs: classify_exit_failure matches only exit code 127 as BinaryNotFound; everything else including signal-killed processes (where status.code() returns None) maps to TransportFailure with 5 retry attempts. Keeping signal kills retryable is correct per spec, but processes killed by SIGSEGV (11) or SIGABRT (6) almost always indicate deterministic bugs (segfaults, assertion failures). Retrying 5 times wastes time and masks the root cause. A warning log when status.code() is None (signal kill) would provide valuable operational signal without changing retry semantics. Minimal code change, clear diagnostic value."},{"amendment_id":"fr-15-34731127","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed critical bug at engine.rs:4643-4644: `let _ = run_snapshot_write.write_run_snapshot(base_dir, project_id, snapshot)` silently discards the Result. The entire crash-resume mechanism depends on this write succeeding — it persists the Failed status and interrupted_run that run resume (line 1155-1158) requires. If this write fails (disk full, I/O error), on-disk state remains Running with no interrupted_run. A subsequent crash during backoff leaves the project stranded: run resume rejects Running status with 'project already has a running run'. This write failure MUST be propagated as fatal. The `let _` pattern here is a genuine defect, not a deliberate choice."},{"amendment_id":"fr-15-bd667ff0","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed at engine.rs:5852-5855: derive_resume_state unconditionally creates the StageCursor with attempt=1, ignoring the interrupted run's actual attempt count. When a crash occurs during the backoff window (between writing the Failed snapshot at line 4643 and restoring Running at line 4672), run resume rebuilds the cursor starting at attempt 1 regardless of prior progress. A stage that was on attempt 4 of 5 gets a full fresh budget of 5 attempts. With repeated crashes during backoff, max_attempts can be exceeded indefinitely. The fix should propagate the attempt count from snapshot.interrupted_run into the rebuilt cursor, using attempt+1 as the starting value for the next attempt."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"ea32758e-6bcd-47eb-8198-f1c45e2e57a8"}
